{"article_id":"jsTPUiiMLdJBq2OB","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senators challenged John Brennan , President Barack Obama ' s nominee","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to lead the CIA ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"about leaks of classified information to journalists , harsh interrogation methods and the legality of targeted drone strikes against U.S. citizens","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"linked to al-Qaeda .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Senator Dianne Feinstein , chairman of the Senate Intelligence committee","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"reviewing Brennan ' s nomination ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"raised the possibility","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"of creating a special court","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"to vet lethal drone strikes ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"while Senator Ron Wyden questioned the basis of \" the president ' s authority","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"to kill Americans . \"","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"Brennan ' s confirmation hearing before the panel yesterday brought fresh scrutiny of the drone program ,","depth":4},{"id":12,"text":"which has been pursued by the White House with limited oversight by Congress or the judiciary .","depth":4},{"id":13,"text":"Senators from both parties prodded Brennan , now the White House counterterrorism adviser , to explain","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"why the administration has been slow to share the legal basis for such strikes , particularly those","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"targeting U.S. citizens .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"\" The president has insisted","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that any actions","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"we take","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"will be legally grounded , \"","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"said Brennan , 57 , an architect of the drone policy .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"the White House has an \" approval process","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"before any action is contemplated ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"including those actions","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that might involve the use of lethal force . \"","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"If confirmed as Central Intelligence Agency director ,","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Brennan said","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"he would ensure","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"\" that any actions","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"we take","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"fully comport with our law \"","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"and at the same time ensure","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"\" that we do everything possible","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"before we need to resort to lethal force . \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"In his opening remarks , he said","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"that \" we remain at war with al-Qaeda and its associated forces","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"which ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"despite the substantial progress","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"we have made against them ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"still seek to carry out deadly strikes against our homeland and our citizens and against our friends and allies . \"","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"The committee will meet again Feb. 12","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"to continue the confirmation hearing in a classified setting .","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"Yesterday ' s three-and-a-half hour session was interrupted several times at the outset by protesters","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"shouting objections to the targeted assassination program as well as to the CIA ' s past use of harsh interrogation methods .","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"Feinstein , a California Democrat , said yesterday","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"she aimed to schedule a vote for Feb. 14 .","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"Brennan , a 25-year veteran of the CIA , spoke briefly about cyber attacks being \" one of the most insidious , one of the most consequential \" threats to U.S. national security .","depth":3},{"id":48,"text":"The hearing also focused on other issues , particularly policies","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"on interrogating terror suspects ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"including the efficacy of so-called enhanced interrogation techniques .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"In December , the committee approved a 6,000-page report on the CIA ' s detention and interrogation policies","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"following the Sept. 11 , 2001 , terrorist attacks .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Brennan said","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"it contradicts some of what he had been told earlier about the value of information","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"obtained","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"using harsh interrogation methods .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"He called \" reprehensible \" the now-prohibited technique of waterboarding , or simulated drowning , during interrogation ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"and said","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"he has \" serious questions \" about its effectiveness .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Brennan said","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"a review of the interrogation program would be his \" highest priority \"","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"if confirmed .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Senator Saxby Chambliss of Georgia , the senior Republican on the committee , pressed Brennan about leaks to the media of classified information ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"including about a foiled bomb plot","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"tied to al-Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"Republicans have complained","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"that some of these leaks ,","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"which took place during the presidential election campaign ,","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"were intended to burnish Obama ' s image .","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"They included articles","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"saying","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"that Obama personally approved drone targets","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"and about the \" Stuxnet \" cyber attack on Iran ' s nuclear program .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"\" I would never provide classified information to reporters , \"","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"Brennan said .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"\" After working in the intelligence profession for 30 years","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"and being at the CIA for 25 years ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"I know the importance","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"of keeping secrets secret . \"","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"U.S. presidents , though , have unlimited authority","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"to declassify information ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"freeing selected members of their administrations to discuss it with reporters","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"without violating the law .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Brennan acknowledged","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"that he has discussed classified information with reporters and editors ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"in part to keep such information out of the public domain .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"At one point , Senator James Risch , an Idaho Republican , accused Brennan of being the source of a leak .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"\" It seems to me ,","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"\"","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Risch said ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"that the source of the leak \" is right here in front of us . \"","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"Wyden , an Oregon Democrat , focused on the administration ' s failure","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"to release to the committee the classified legal opinions","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"underpinning the president ' s authority","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to conduct strikes , particularly against U.S. citizens .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"Earlier this week , Obama ordered the Justice Department to provide members of the House and Senate intelligence panels with one such document , a classified justification for drone strikes against U.S. citizens abroad","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"who are found to be terrorists .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"Wyden told Brennan yesterday","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that \" giving any president unfettered power","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"to kill an American","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"without checks and balances \"","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"is troubling .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"The radical cleric and U.S. citizen Anwar al-Awlaki was killed in a 2011 drone strike in Yemen along with an alleged al-Qaeda propagandist Samir Khan , 25 , a Saudi-born American of Pakistani heritage .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"Two weeks later , al-Awlaki ' s 16-year-old , Denver-born son , Abdulrahman , was killed in a suspected drone strike in Yemen .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Brennan said","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"al-Awlaki was involved in numerous plots","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"to kill Americans ,","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"including a 2010 attempt","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"to blow up two U.S.- bound cargo planes with bombs","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"hidden inside laser-printer cartridges .","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"After Wyden asked","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"if drone targets were given a chance","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"to surrender ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"Brennan said","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"that any American","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"who joins al-Qaeda","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"\" should know well","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"that they , in fact , are part of an enemy against us","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"and that the United States will do everything possible","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"to destroy that enemy","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"to save American lives . \"","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"Brennan said","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"the pilotless planes are used only as a \" last resort . \"","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Senator Susan Collins , a Maine Republican , said","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"that the Obama administration has conducted four times as many drone strikes","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"as the administration of President George W. Bush had .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"She asked","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"whether there was a connection to the termination of the CIA ' s detention program .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"\" There ' s never been an occasion","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"that I ' m aware of","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"where we had the opportunity","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"to capture a terrorist","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"and we didn ' t","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"and we decided to take a lethal strike , \"","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Brennan said .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"He added","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"there was no correlation between the termination of CIA detention program and the increase in strikes .","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"Feinstein said","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"she would review proposals","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"to create a court similar to the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"\" to ensure","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"that drone strikes are carried out in a manner consistent with our values \"","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"and \" to review the conduct of such strikes . \"","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"\" This has gone about as far","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"as it can go","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"as a covert activity , \"","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"she said of the drone program .","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"\" There ' s an absence","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"of knowing exactly who is responsible for what decision .","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"I think","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"we need to look at this whole process","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"and figure a way","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"to make it transparent and identifiable . \"","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":307,"left":194,"right":306,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":164,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":157,"right":163,"relation":"el